##Topics Covered
## What is DOM (Document Object Model)?
DOM stands for Document Object Model.
It is a programming interface that represents an HTML document as a tree of objects.
JavaScript uses the DOM to access, modify, add, or remove HTML elements dynamically.
Why DOM is Important?
Change text dynamically.
Change CSS styles.
Add or remove HTML elements.
Create interactive websites.
  ##Types of Nodes
Every object inside the DOM is called a Node.
Types of Nodes
##Element Node
Represents HTML tags.
Example:
<h1>Hello</h1>
<p>Welcome</p>
<h1> and <p> are Element Nodes.
## Text Node
Represents the text inside an element.
Example:
<h1>Hello Akshita</h1>
Here,
Hello Akshita
is a Text Node.
##Attribute Node
Represents attributes of an element.
Example
<img src="image.png" alt="Image">
Here,
src
alt
are Attribute Nodes.
## Comment Node
Represents comments.
<!-- This is a comment -->
