## innerHTML
Definition
innerHTML changes or reads the content inside an HTML element.
HTML
<h2 id="demo">Hello</h2>

<button onclick="changeText()">Click</button>
JavaScript
function changeText(){

document.getElementById("demo").innerHTML="Welcome to JavaScript";

}
Output
Before
Hello
After
Welcome to JavaScript
4. outerHTML
Definition
outerHTML replaces the entire HTML element.
HTML
<h2 id="demo">Hello</h2>
JavaScript
document.getElementById("demo").outerHTML="<h1>Welcome</h1>";
Output
<h1>Welcome</h1>
The <h2> element is completely replaced by <h1>.
Difference
innerHTML
outerHTML
Changes only the content inside an element
Replaces the entire element
Element remains the same
Element itself changes
##DOM + CSS
JavaScript can also change CSS properties using the DOM.
HTML
<h1 id="heading">Hello Akshita</h1>

<button onclick="changeColor()">Click</button>
CSS
#heading{
color:blue;
font-size:35px;
}
JavaScript
function changeColor(){

document.getElementById("heading").style.color="red";

document.getElementById("heading").style.fontSize="50px";

}
